<br>
Epic level ---  % Boost<br>
0        0<br>
10        10<br>
20        18<br>
30        25<br>
40        31<br>
50        35<br>
60        39<br>
70        42<br>
80        45<br>
90        47<br>
100        50<br>
<br>
Basically, the difference between epic levels diminishes as the epic levels increase.<br>
<br>
Going from 0 (no raiding) to 50 (old world dragons) is a 35% jump.<br>
<br>
Going from 50 (Old dragons) to 100 (absolute end game) is only a 15% jump.<br>
<br>
This might work better. <br>
<br>
The numbers are still pretty high overall, really. This isn't a conservative thing. It's really a bit late in the game to be talking about something like this, so I don't think the idea would fly.<br>
<br>
I still stand by the idea that not all experience is created equal, though. It makes sense to me that boss experience should be separate from normal experience, and provide separate benefits. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uraticus7th.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raticus 7th</A> at: 3/22/02 4:25:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ullanoldarlluindar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llanoldar Lluindar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 8:10:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22978.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Here is what i foresee as the problem and why something like this will probably never be implemented.<br>
<br>
How do you determine who gets the epic xp?<br>
<br>
Here's a few cases:<br>
<br>
1.  All who aggro the mob.  Problems?  Now theres 50 n00bs running around tagging along on raids lagging people up to get epic xp and doing nothing good.<br>
<br>
2.  Create a special kind of grouping for raids.  Problems?  Its feasible what with new raid channel code and stuff, but very complicated i would guess.<br>
<br>
3.  Only people in groups fighting the mob.  Problems?  What if there are people without groups?  It can happen.<br>
<br>
4.  Only members of first guild to engage the mob (resets when aggro/all the guildies die).  Prevents other guilds from ks'ing but theres too many guild alliances out there for this to be practical.<br>
<br>
